This paper investigates potential factors associated with gender discrimination in collaborative recommender systems. The study focuses on analyzing user profiles and their characteristics, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). The paper also discusses legal and ethical issues related to fairness and equity, which are relevant to social and information sciences (cs.SI). Additionally, the study involves analyzing user behavior and trust in the system, which are relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and software engineering (cs.SD).
